    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Read and re-read again I did not find any obvious flaw that will break.\r\n\r\nGood to know. Given the current context, which is modifying the parameters before sending the request, it will be fine indeed. But what you introduce some async in there :) Like for example you do a first query to check another index, and then you trigger the search. The code will go on and change back the reference to the search function. In this case we might end up in a loopy situation :)\r\n\r\nKnowing the caveat, we are able to document that though. WDYT? @vvo ",
