    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Well it's possible as long as you are aware that the ref to the method will change and that you have to bind the reference to the search method yourself.\r\n\r\nA very naive example of delay:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nsearchFunction: function(helper) {\r\n  const search = helper.search.bind(helper);\r\n  setTimeout(function(){\r\n    search();\r\n  }, 10);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis would work. What about we provide the search method as a standalone function along the helper? (this is one of the point I want to discuss Thursday)",
